    "comment": "Rationale: Fig 5 shows localisation of TNK2 (ACK1) to both axon terminals and dendritic spines using DAB immunolocalization in mouse hippocampus, neocortex and cerebellum. As the molecule does not contain a transmembrane domain or membrane binding motif, its localisation is cytosolic.. Experimental description: M&M:\" Adult mice (NMRI mice). \"\n\n\"incubated with rabbit antibody to Ack1/Pyk1 (1:100) for 2 days at 4°C.\" \"Two rabbit polyclonal antibodies (384 and 385) were generated using the GST fusion proteins corresponding to the proline-rich region (amino acids 502-1008) following standard protocols (Harlow, 1988).\"",
